Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and slice @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Quarter @lime{1}. Gently crush @peanuts{1%ounce} in their #bag{}.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} (large #pot{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add chicken and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} (the chicken will finish cooking in the next step).

Break @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce} in half and add to pan with chicken mixture.

Increase heat to high; stir in @tangy tamarind sauce{4%ounce} and @water{2%cups} (3 cups for 4 servings). Cook, stirring constantly (separating noodles as you stir), until noodles are tender and sauce has thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

When noodles have 1 minute remaining, add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings) to pan. Cook, stirring, until veggies are just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. (If mixture seems dry, add a splash of water.) Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide stir-fry between shallow #bowls{}; squeeze one lime wedge (two wedges for 4) over bowls. Sprinkle peanuts over stir-fry. Serve with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} and remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.